Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo Osun State Governor, Adegboyega Oyetola, on Monday approved the appointment of 36 people as chairmen and members of the rent tribunals for the nine federal constituencies in the state. A statement by the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor, Ismail Omipidan, explained that the appointment was in accordance with the Residential Accommodation (Rent Control) Law Cap. 144 Laws of Osun, 2002, Section 5(1)(a) and (b). Omipidan added that Oyetola, in constituting the rent tribunals, wanted to enhance communal peace and dispensation of justice in landlord/tenant related disputes. He added that through the rent tribunals, peaceful and amicable resolution of rent-related issues would be guaranteed in all the federal constituencies. The statement said the appointments took immediate effect. The chairmen of the tribunal in the nine federal constituencies include, Osogbo Federal Constituency, N.O. Sanusi; Ijesa South Federal Constituency, Ayo Afilaka; Ede Federal Constituency, Kunle Abbas; Ifelodun Federal Constituency,Â  Kayode Adebisi, and Ila Federal Constituency, Segun Durotolu. Copyright PUNCH.
